{"id":4677,"date":"2021-05-10T11:08:52","date_gmt":"2021-05-10T09:08:52","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/154.0.202.153\/?post_type=dt_team&#038;p=4677"},"modified":"2021-08-17T09:38:54","modified_gmt":"2021-08-17T07:38:54","slug":"ankama-samuel","status":"publish","type":"dt_team","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/dt_team\/ankama-samuel\/","title":{"rendered":"Ankama, Samuel"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4678\" src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/148_hon__samuel_chief_ankama.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"137\" height=\"204\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"contact-position\">Deputy Minister: Office of the Prime Minister<\/p>\n<div class=\"contact-address clearafter\">\n<p><span class=\"jicons-text\">Address:<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"contact-country\">SWAPO<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"contact-contactinfo clearafter\">\n<p class=\"contact-webpage\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.opm.gov.na\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">http:\/\/www.opm.gov.na<\/a><\/p>\n<h3 id=\"display-misc\" class=\"title pane-toggler-down\"><a>Other information<\/a><\/h3>\n<div class=\"pane-slider content pane-down\">\n<div class=\"contact-miscinfo\">\n<p><span class=\"jicons-text\">Other information:<\/span><\/p>\n<table width=\"100%\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"25%\"><strong>Legislative Profile<\/strong><\/td>\n<td>Member of Parliament since 2005; Member of SWAPO central Committee since 2007; Member of SWAPO Party Think Tank since 2008; Deputy Minister of Works and Transport 2010 &#8211; 2012; Deputy Minister of Fisheries and Marine Resources since December 2013 -2018; Deputy Minister in the Office of Prime Minister since February 2018.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Personal<\/strong><\/td>\n<td>Born on 27 October 1957 at Otshaandja, Oshakati West, Oshana Region<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Education<\/strong><\/td>\n<td>Attended Kindergarten and Primary Education at Uuladhi Roman Catholic School and Oniimwandi Government School respectively 1967 &#8211; 1975; Form 1 at Ombalantu\/David Sheehama SSS and banned never to attend any other school by the apartheid system 1976; Standard 8 Certificate through distance education 1978; Matriculation Certificate through distance education 1982;Primary Education Certificate at Ongwediva Teachers&#8217; Training Centre 1980; Diploma in Expert Photography at Africa United Colleges (RSA) 1983; Certificate in Youth Ministry at Khanyisa Institute of Southern Africa, Durban under the Southern Africa Catholic Bishops&#8217; Conference 1984; Bachelor of Education in English Language Teaching at University of Edinburgh (Scotland) 1989; Masters of Arts in Education with specialization in English Language Teaching at University of Warwick (UK) 1996; PhD in Language, Literacy and Culture at University of Maryland, Baltimore County (UMBC), USA 2001 &#8211; 2003;Certificate in Defense and Security Management at Witwatersrand University (RSA) 2005.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Career<\/strong><\/td>\n<td>Teacher at Oniimwandi LP (1977 &#8211; 1978) Okatana SP (1982 &#8211; 1983) Iipumbu SSS (1990 &#8211; 1995); Lecturer at Ongwediva Teachers&#8217; Training College 1985; Facilitator for English Senior Secondary Education for Ondangwa West 1993 &#8211; 1995; Education Officer 1995 &#8211; 1998; Lecturer at University of Namibia (UNAM) Northern Campus (Head of Department 1999) 1998 &#8211; 1999; Deputy Director of UNAM Northern Campus 2000 &#8211; 2001.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Interests<\/strong><\/td>\n<td>Photography &amp; Filming (editing); Music (Keyboard player); Computing; Travel; Community Service<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Deputy Minister: Office of the Prime Minister Address: SWAPO http:\/\/www.opm.gov.na Other information Other information: Legislative Profile Member of Parlia